 \textbf{Autonomous locomotion for virtual characters in constrained environments}.
 This thesis objective is to improve the motion autonomy of virtual characters interacting with
 complex environments. We consider acyclic motions, such as reaching or climbing tasks (as opposed to cyclic
 motions such as walking or running), and propose new methods and heuristics to synthesize, in real-time, believable motions, based
 on short-time contact planning.

